WEBVTT

00:06.083 --> 00:08.083
[menacing music playing]

00:15.125 --> 00:18.583
[teenage girl] "It began as a prank
and ended in murder."

00:19.333 --> 00:21.041
Fantastic choice.

00:21.125 --> 00:22.458
I love this one.

00:22.541 --> 00:23.833
It's trash.

00:23.916 --> 00:25.708
Low-brow horror.

00:25.791 --> 00:27.416
It's for my stepdaughter.

00:27.500 --> 00:29.583
[sighs] That'll be $2.95.

00:30.250 --> 00:32.750
Thank you for shopping at B. Dalton's.

00:32.833 --> 00:35.125
[pleasant Muzak playing over speakers]

00:35.208 --> 00:37.000
And have a nice night.

00:37.833 --> 00:39.666
[man over PA] Attention, shoppers.

00:39.750 --> 00:42.708
The Shadyside Mall is now closed.

00:42.791 --> 00:45.875
The Shadyside Mall is now closed.

00:45.958 --> 00:49.166
["Closer" playing over store speakers]
♪ You let me violate you ♪

00:51.083 --> 00:53.458
♪ You let me desecrate you ♪

00:56.541 --> 00:59.041
♪ You let me penetrate you… ♪

00:59.125 --> 01:00.333
[sighs]

01:00.416 --> 01:02.000
[telephone ringing]

01:02.750 --> 01:04.125
[telephone ringing]

01:04.208 --> 01:06.833
Hello, this is B. Dalton's. We're closed.

01:07.416 --> 01:09.791
OK, since when do you work late?

01:09.875 --> 01:12.583
Since my mom used her last paycheck
on scratch tickets

01:12.666 --> 01:14.208
instead of the gas bill.

01:14.291 --> 01:15.333
[line goes dead]

01:16.250 --> 01:17.083
Hello?

01:17.916 --> 01:18.875
Ryan?

01:18.958 --> 01:20.416
Ryan? Are you there?

01:21.416 --> 01:24.000
-Ryan? Hello?
-[dead tone]

01:24.750 --> 01:27.083
Hello, Ryan!

01:28.500 --> 01:30.083
[suspenseful music playing]

01:37.333 --> 01:38.291
-[clanging]
-[gasps]

01:40.083 --> 01:40.958
Night.

01:42.166 --> 01:43.166
[relieved sigh]

01:47.208 --> 01:49.541
-[falsetto] All alone now!
-Jesus Christ!

01:49.625 --> 01:51.125
Woo-hoo! [laughing]

01:51.208 --> 01:53.875
Ryan! What the hell, dude! [gasps]

01:53.958 --> 01:55.250
Forgive me.

01:55.333 --> 01:58.500
I do need a ride tonight.

01:58.583 --> 01:59.958
That's what she said.

02:00.041 --> 02:01.750
You are disgusting.

02:02.333 --> 02:04.833
And, yes, I don't want to walk home alone.

02:05.333 --> 02:09.583
Fine. Just give me and, uh… Jasmine here
15 minutes to close up.

02:10.208 --> 02:11.541
You gave her a name.

02:11.625 --> 02:15.500
Yeah, I thought, uh… "Big Tits"
was kind of deflating her ego.

02:15.583 --> 02:16.583
[she scoffs]

02:20.166 --> 02:21.958
-[whispering voice] Ryan…
-What?

02:24.166 --> 02:25.791
I didn't say anything, weirdo.

02:29.625 --> 02:31.041
[suspenseful music playing]

02:31.125 --> 02:32.750
[shutter creaking]

02:38.000 --> 02:39.000
[groans]

02:43.250 --> 02:45.125
[ominous drumbeat]

02:45.958 --> 02:48.041
[suspenseful music continues]

02:54.750 --> 02:56.208
-[sighs]
-[distant bang]

02:57.333 --> 02:58.333
[gasps]

03:13.583 --> 03:14.750
[sighs]

03:14.833 --> 03:15.708
[high-pitched shrill]

03:15.791 --> 03:16.791
[gasps]

03:19.875 --> 03:20.875
Hello?

03:24.750 --> 03:26.500
[ominous music playing]

03:32.333 --> 03:33.333
[relieved sigh]

03:34.625 --> 03:36.208
-[object falls]
-[gasps]

03:38.416 --> 03:40.750
[forcefully] OK. Very funny, asshole.

03:40.833 --> 03:42.583
I'm spooked, OK? You win.

03:44.583 --> 03:45.416
Ryan?

03:47.166 --> 03:49.791
[ominous music playing]

03:53.625 --> 03:54.791
[breathes deeply]

03:56.750 --> 03:59.333
[she screams]

04:00.833 --> 04:02.208
[she pants]

04:04.625 --> 04:05.458
[screams]

04:06.041 --> 04:07.416
[she grunts]

04:09.083 --> 04:10.958
[shouting] Ryan! Ryan!

04:11.041 --> 04:12.416
Help!

04:14.916 --> 04:17.791
Ryan! [gasping]

04:17.875 --> 04:18.875
Oh!

04:18.958 --> 04:21.125
[panting]

04:26.875 --> 04:27.958
[ringing tone]

04:28.041 --> 04:29.750
[woman] 911, what's your emergency?

04:29.833 --> 04:32.125
Hi, um… I'm in the Shadyside Mall.

04:32.208 --> 04:33.541
-Um…
-[footsteps squeaking]

04:33.625 --> 04:34.833
[woman] Hello?

04:34.916 --> 04:35.958
[Heather pants]

04:36.041 --> 04:36.958
[woman] Hello?

04:37.625 --> 04:39.166
Are you still there, ma'am?

04:39.750 --> 04:40.791
Is someone hurt?

04:41.291 --> 04:43.833
Ma'am, if you don't answer,
I'm gonna dispatch help.

04:45.958 --> 04:47.458
[ominous music playing]

05:02.125 --> 05:03.416
[gasps]

05:07.458 --> 05:09.666
[breathing shakily]

05:21.333 --> 05:23.291
[shouting]

05:29.500 --> 05:31.541
[panting]

05:34.375 --> 05:35.375
[she gasps]

05:38.166 --> 05:39.041
[gasps]

05:39.125 --> 05:43.333
[she breathes heavily]

05:54.500 --> 05:58.375
[ominous music crescendos]

06:00.708 --> 06:02.250
[doll hissing]

06:02.333 --> 06:03.250
[Heather] Hey!

06:06.666 --> 06:07.791
[Heather gasping]

06:07.875 --> 06:09.750
Help! Help!

06:09.833 --> 06:11.416
[Heather screaming]

06:11.500 --> 06:14.958
[menacing music playing]

06:18.333 --> 06:19.750
[screams]

06:21.791 --> 06:23.166
Help!

06:29.958 --> 06:31.416
[screams]

06:31.500 --> 06:35.875
[dramatic music playing]

06:35.958 --> 06:37.583
[she screams]

06:40.458 --> 06:41.458
Ah!

06:41.541 --> 06:42.833
Ah, ah!

06:50.541 --> 06:51.541
Ryan?

06:53.666 --> 06:57.625
[crying] Please! It's me. It's me.

06:58.375 --> 06:59.458
[gunshot]

07:07.250 --> 07:10.166
[Heather gasps]

07:14.166 --> 07:15.083
[officer gasps]

07:29.708 --> 07:33.416
[dramatic music playing]

07:39.250 --> 07:41.833
[female reporter 1]
More death in Shadyside

07:41.916 --> 07:46.958
while Sunnyvale enters its 30th year
with no violent crime.

07:50.375 --> 07:54.208
[female reporter 2] Killer Capital, USA,
as tragedy struck again.

07:55.166 --> 07:58.916
[male sports announcer]
Sunnyvale football wins again!

07:59.000 --> 08:01.000
[female reporter 3]
Christina Marlow and Jessica Van

08:01.083 --> 08:03.541
were found in a house
in a residential area near Shadyside.

08:03.625 --> 08:04.958
They've been identified.

08:08.458 --> 08:09.791
[woman 1] That's Sunnyvale!

08:09.875 --> 08:13.708
[man 1] Shadysiders seem to have
no desire to better themselves.

08:13.791 --> 08:16.083
[man 2] Sunnyvale and Shadyside!

08:19.083 --> 08:20.666
[male reporter 1] This just in!

08:21.416 --> 08:25.500
More body parts found in the lake
between Shadyside and Sunnyvale.

08:28.416 --> 08:30.916
[male announcer 1] Sunnyvale voted
Most Beautiful Place to Live!

08:31.000 --> 08:32.583
[male reporter 2] Shadyside residents

08:32.666 --> 08:34.875
are spending another night hunkering down
in darkness as…

08:34.958 --> 08:37.375
[male announcer 2]
Find your new home in Sunnyvale,

08:37.458 --> 08:41.125
where the sun always shines,
even when it's cloudy!

08:41.208 --> 08:44.041
While the depression hit Shadyside hard,

08:44.125 --> 08:47.708
the economy in Sunnyvale
continues to shine.

08:49.041 --> 08:51.625
[female reporter 4] According to sources
with the Shadyside Police…

08:51.708 --> 08:53.333
[indistinct news coverage]

09:00.500 --> 09:01.916
[girl screams]

09:04.333 --> 09:05.916
[crowd shouting]

09:06.000 --> 09:09.041
[high-pitched shrill]

09:10.083 --> 09:12.166
[woman screams]

09:12.250 --> 09:16.250
["Only Happy When It Rains" playing]
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

09:17.041 --> 09:20.500
♪ I'm only happy when it's complicated ♪

09:21.041 --> 09:24.791
♪ And though I know
You can't appreciate it ♪

09:24.875 --> 09:28.000
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

09:28.875 --> 09:32.500
♪ You know I love it
When the news is bad ♪

09:33.041 --> 09:36.166
♪ Why it feels so good to feel so sad? ♪

09:36.833 --> 09:40.125
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

09:45.625 --> 09:48.125
[alarm bell ringing]

09:52.458 --> 09:55.458
Shadyside, small-town America.

09:55.541 --> 09:59.916
But among locals, a history of horror
has earned it another nickname,

10:00.000 --> 10:02.125
"Killer Capital USA."

10:02.208 --> 10:05.041
-And last night, tragedy struck again.
-Ugh, Dad!

10:05.125 --> 10:09.041
I'm here with Sheriff Nick Goode.
Sheriff, what can you tell us?

10:10.291 --> 10:12.416
Uh, there were seven victims,

10:12.500 --> 10:15.416
uh, ages, uh, 16 to 42.

10:15.500 --> 10:18.000
Uh, the perpetrator's also deceased.

10:18.083 --> 10:20.500
[female reporter]
Shadyside sits just beside Sunnyvale,

10:20.583 --> 10:23.291
one of the safest and wealthiest
communities in the country…

10:23.375 --> 10:24.416
Josh!

10:24.500 --> 10:27.708
What is it about Shadyside?
How do we end this cycle of violence?

10:27.791 --> 10:28.958
[girl] Josh!

10:29.458 --> 10:34.041
["Fear of the Dark"
playing over headphones]

10:34.125 --> 10:37.458
-♪ I am a man who walks alone… ♪
-[keyboard clicking]

10:37.541 --> 10:40.791
♪ And when I'm walking a dark road ♪

10:40.875 --> 10:44.083
♪ At night
Or strolling through the park… ♪

10:44.166 --> 10:45.250
[chat beeps]

10:46.083 --> 10:47.208
[chat beeps]

10:47.291 --> 10:50.375
♪ When the light begins to change ♪

10:50.458 --> 10:53.708
♪ I sometimes feel a little strange ♪

10:53.791 --> 10:57.083
♪ A little anxious when it's dark ♪

10:57.166 --> 11:01.708
-[music fades out]
-[suspenseful music playing]

11:04.916 --> 11:05.916
[chat beeps]

11:06.000 --> 11:07.875
[tense music playing]

11:23.125 --> 11:24.458
[keyboard clicking]

11:39.958 --> 11:43.583
-Dude! What the hell?
-This isn't yours, dillweed!

11:43.666 --> 11:46.416
Oh, I get it.
You building a shrine or something?

11:46.500 --> 11:48.875
Alright, you know what?
It's time for school. Get in the car.

11:48.958 --> 11:50.791
-Let me finish this chat.
-[she tuts]

11:51.625 --> 11:53.125
Deena, be careful with that!

11:53.208 --> 11:56.416
Dad said you weren't allowed on this.
Know how expensive AOL is?

11:56.500 --> 11:58.541
I'm stealing it. I'm talking to someone!

11:58.625 --> 12:01.416
This internet bullshit
is exactly why you have no friends.

12:01.500 --> 12:05.208
It's not bullshit.
It's a community dedicated to the truth.

12:05.291 --> 12:09.208
Look, some guy went crazy and killed
a bunch of people at the mall last night.

12:09.875 --> 12:10.875
Holy shit.

12:10.958 --> 12:12.625
[Josh] It was all over the news.

12:13.708 --> 12:15.000
Skull mask killer.

12:15.666 --> 12:19.666
But, of course, the media won't talk
about the most important part.

12:20.375 --> 12:22.208
[Deena] Josh, I am telling you calmly,

12:22.291 --> 12:25.625
step out of your internet fantasy
nerd land and get in the car.

12:25.708 --> 12:28.250
Step out your depressoid
"I'm gonna die alone" land,

12:28.333 --> 12:30.208
and stop obsessing about Sam!

12:30.291 --> 12:31.916
-Get in the car!
-[bangs desk]

12:33.083 --> 12:35.916
[ominous music playing]

12:36.708 --> 12:39.791
["Machinehead" playing]

12:39.875 --> 12:42.041
[school bell rings]

12:43.333 --> 12:45.166
[indistinct chatter]

12:46.916 --> 12:49.166
♪ Breathe in, breathe out… ♪

12:49.250 --> 12:52.375
See you later, Sir Silence.

12:55.375 --> 12:57.333
♪ Breathe in, breathe out ♪

12:57.416 --> 12:59.583
♪ Breathe in, breathe out ♪

13:00.916 --> 13:04.416
["Damn I Wish I Was Your Lover" playing]

13:06.416 --> 13:10.166
Up, up, down, down.
Left, right, left, right, B, A, start.

13:10.916 --> 13:14.583
♪ Damn, I wish I was your lover… ♪

13:15.416 --> 13:16.500
[boy] Watch it, nerd.

13:17.000 --> 13:21.916
["Sour Times" playing]
♪ 'Cause nobody loves me, it's true ♪

13:24.208 --> 13:27.041
♪ Not like you do ♪

13:37.833 --> 13:39.333
[girl] Jeez.

13:39.416 --> 13:42.125
[indistinct chatter]

13:45.666 --> 13:47.708
[random student shouts, laughs]

13:54.375 --> 13:56.583
You see? It's the witch.

13:56.666 --> 13:57.958
Sarah Fier's back.

13:58.041 --> 14:00.916
Oh, Christ. Not you too.

14:01.000 --> 14:02.500
[cheerleader laughs]

14:07.250 --> 14:09.375
[school bell rings]

14:10.250 --> 14:15.208
"She reaches from beyond the grave
to make good men her wicked slaves!"

14:15.291 --> 14:16.916
-"She'll take your blood!"
-[Deena] Simon!

14:17.000 --> 14:20.500
"She'll take your head.
She'll follow you until you're dead!"

14:20.583 --> 14:21.791
Wow!

14:21.875 --> 14:23.375
You guys are dicks.

14:23.458 --> 14:25.333
-It's just fun.
-It's sick.

14:25.416 --> 14:28.416
What? The dude was wearing
a Halloween skull mask!

14:29.000 --> 14:30.458
How is that not fun?

14:30.541 --> 14:32.083
People died.

14:32.166 --> 14:33.500
Heather died.

14:33.583 --> 14:38.708
The dude was probably just some sad sack
who hated his life, like the rest of us,

14:38.791 --> 14:41.916
except he decided, "Hey,
why don't I get out of here for good?"

14:42.000 --> 14:45.708
And, "Hey, why don't I take Heather
and a couple other mall rats with me?"

14:45.791 --> 14:48.666
There's no angry dead witch
who made him go postal.

14:48.750 --> 14:51.541
The only thing that made him go crazy
is this town!

14:54.916 --> 14:56.041
Are you OK?

14:56.125 --> 14:58.250
Yeah, I'm fine.

14:58.875 --> 15:01.500
Seems like…
maybe you got a little witch in you.

15:01.583 --> 15:02.750
[cheerleader laughs]

15:02.833 --> 15:06.375
Dude, why are you even in here?
This is the girls' bathroom.

15:10.833 --> 15:12.000
Candy store.

15:12.083 --> 15:14.625
You know we don't believe
this witch shit, right?

15:14.708 --> 15:17.583
It's just, like, fucked-up Santa Claus
or something.

15:17.666 --> 15:19.041
[Simon] Ho, ho, ho!

15:20.041 --> 15:22.666
-What's this?
-I need you to give this to Sam tonight.

15:22.750 --> 15:24.833
-Yeah, uh-uh. No way.
-Come on, Kate!

15:24.916 --> 15:26.375
No way, Deena.

15:26.458 --> 15:29.875
I am not getting mixed up
in your ex drama. Do it yourself.

15:29.958 --> 15:32.875
I'm not going to the game. I quit band.

15:32.958 --> 15:35.541
-Since when?
-Since who gives a shit!

15:35.625 --> 15:37.875
Was band the only extracurricular
you had left?

15:39.625 --> 15:41.666
You still have your band uniform, right?

15:41.750 --> 15:44.333
You just wear that shit one last time.

15:46.833 --> 15:50.000
I've got something
that'll give you the balls to face Sam.

15:52.916 --> 15:57.583
What? You're dealing again? I thought you
stopped after this dingus's brother OD'd.

15:58.083 --> 15:59.083
[Simon] Timothy?

15:59.166 --> 16:01.708
Wh… Uh… Timmy wasn't a real OD.

16:01.791 --> 16:03.000
He didn't actually die.

16:03.583 --> 16:04.708
They brought him back.

16:05.250 --> 16:06.375
Ja-jing!

16:06.875 --> 16:08.041
You're both morons.

16:08.125 --> 16:10.583
Which one of us is valedictorian, again?

16:10.666 --> 16:13.541
President of every club
this shithole has to offer.

16:14.416 --> 16:18.000
I'm getting out of here. Off to claim
my place among the stars, bitch.

16:18.083 --> 16:21.291
[boy] Woo! The witch lives!
Long live Sarah Fier!

16:21.375 --> 16:22.458
Woo!

16:22.541 --> 16:24.250
Woo!

16:25.208 --> 16:26.541
Yeah!

16:26.625 --> 16:28.208
[students laughing, shouting]

16:28.291 --> 16:29.250
[Simon laughs]

16:29.333 --> 16:30.708
[coach] Before tonight's game,

16:30.791 --> 16:33.750
out of respect
for last night's tragic events,

16:33.833 --> 16:37.000
Sunnyvale will host
a candlelight vigil for the victims.

16:37.083 --> 16:40.625
All player, cheer and band attendance
is mandatory.

16:40.708 --> 16:42.666
[male student] Oh, really? Come on!

16:42.750 --> 16:46.375
["Insane in the Membrane" playing]
♪ Don't you know I'm loco? ♪

16:46.458 --> 16:49.375
[indistinct chatter]

16:49.458 --> 16:50.708
[barking]

16:50.791 --> 16:52.458
♪ Insane in the membrane… ♪

16:52.541 --> 16:53.750
Didn't you quit?

16:53.833 --> 16:55.541
♪ Insane in the brain… ♪

16:55.625 --> 16:58.666
-[Simon growls]
-♪ Insane in the membrane ♪

16:58.750 --> 17:00.500
♪ Insane in the brain ♪

17:01.083 --> 17:03.250
♪ Insane in the membrane ♪

17:03.333 --> 17:05.458
♪ Crazy insane, got no brain ♪

17:05.541 --> 17:07.583
["Creep" playing over headphones]

17:07.666 --> 17:10.583
♪ You're so very special ♪

17:13.166 --> 17:14.750
♪ But I'm a creep ♪

17:18.166 --> 17:21.208
♪ I'm a weirdo ♪

17:23.041 --> 17:26.541
♪ What the hell am I doing here? ♪

17:28.833 --> 17:31.291
♪ I don't belong here ♪

17:34.125 --> 17:36.208
♪ I don't care if it hurts… ♪
[music fades]

17:36.291 --> 17:41.083
[uplifting music playing] ♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

17:45.625 --> 17:49.125
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

17:51.166 --> 17:53.833
[man 1 over speakers] This isn't
how I wanted to be here tonight.

17:55.291 --> 17:57.333
I wanted to be here as a fan.

17:58.916 --> 18:02.333
Our Sunnyvale Devils
and your Shadyside Witches

18:02.416 --> 18:05.083
throwing down
some good old American football.

18:06.041 --> 18:08.458
Instead I find myself here

18:09.416 --> 18:10.625
as a husband,

18:10.708 --> 18:12.833
a father, as a neighbor.

18:12.916 --> 18:14.416
And, yes,

18:14.500 --> 18:16.333
mayor of Sunnyvale.

18:18.666 --> 18:21.791
And on behalf of all of the people
in my town,

18:21.875 --> 18:26.875
I say all of Sunnyvale mourns with you.

18:26.958 --> 18:29.416
Yeah, really looks like they give a damn.

18:29.500 --> 18:32.791
The only Sunnyvalers who came
were the ones who had to.

18:33.291 --> 18:35.583
The football team and the cheerleaders.

18:38.333 --> 18:41.125
[mayor] Our hearts are broken with grief.

18:41.208 --> 18:44.708
[melancholic music playing]

19:09.875 --> 19:11.791
[lighter clinks]

19:17.250 --> 19:18.083
Sam.

19:21.833 --> 19:22.958
[breathes deeply]

19:23.041 --> 19:26.666
[soft music playing]

19:26.750 --> 19:28.333
I didn't think you were coming.

19:29.625 --> 19:30.958
I thought you quit band.

19:31.625 --> 19:34.000
Yeah, I did. Here.

19:37.666 --> 19:38.500
What…

19:47.250 --> 19:48.500
Is this my stuff?

19:50.375 --> 19:51.625
Ding ding ding.

19:53.833 --> 19:56.083
[dramatic music playing]

20:00.166 --> 20:02.875
[man 2 over speakers] My family's been
in Sunnyvale for generations,

20:02.958 --> 20:04.958
and now my brother is mayor

20:05.750 --> 20:07.000
and I your sheriff.

20:08.083 --> 20:09.541
We've prospered here.

20:10.541 --> 20:13.791
And yet, I've seen you,
our neighbors in Shadyside,

20:13.875 --> 20:16.291
suffer tragedy after tragedy.

20:16.958 --> 20:21.458
It's easy in times like this
to drown in questions of why…

20:22.291 --> 20:24.083
Why this happened.

20:24.166 --> 20:26.666
But I know too well

20:27.791 --> 20:31.000
there are no answers
that will provide relief.

20:31.583 --> 20:33.875
There's no peace found in the past.

20:34.583 --> 20:36.250
-Can we talk for a second?
-No.

20:36.333 --> 20:40.500
You broke up with me! Remember?
So stop acting like I'm the bad guy.

20:41.291 --> 20:43.625
Yeah, well, I'm not the one
who moved to Sunnyvale.

20:44.208 --> 20:46.583
OK, you made the choice.
I just made it official.

20:47.291 --> 20:49.458
My parents got divorced.

