39:04.291 --> 39:06.666
[Sam] He has been with me all night!

39:06.750 --> 39:10.416
-Stop covering for him! He's a bad guy.
-You're out of control!

39:10.500 --> 39:13.500
You put me in the hospital!
Now you're here yelling at me--

39:13.583 --> 39:17.958
OK. No, that was an accident.
Look, I got a nosebleed.

39:18.041 --> 39:21.083
-I didn't actually mean--
-A nosebleed? Stop making excuses!

39:21.583 --> 39:23.625
You are total chaos!

39:23.708 --> 39:25.166
And you have always been!

39:25.250 --> 39:30.333
So don't blame me when you wake up
in ten years just like your dad!

39:30.416 --> 39:32.916
Old and drunk and going nowhere!

39:33.000 --> 39:35.000
OK, first, go to hell.

39:35.083 --> 39:38.791
Second, yeah.
Congrats on getting out of Shadyside, Sam.

39:38.875 --> 39:42.958
All you had to do was suck it up,
literally, and swallow some Sunnyvale--

39:43.041 --> 39:46.166
You know what?
I never want to see you again!

39:46.250 --> 39:48.333
Great. Have a nice goddamn life!

39:48.416 --> 39:50.500
[Peter groans, gurgles]

39:54.625 --> 39:56.166
[Deena] Oh my God!

39:56.250 --> 39:57.833
[girls screaming]

40:04.583 --> 40:09.041
-Where'd you learn how to do this?
-Oh, a lot of people trade hacks online.

40:09.125 --> 40:10.250
[coughs] Nerd.

40:13.041 --> 40:14.875
So, um… [chuckles]

40:14.958 --> 40:16.916
…when'd you get into the fruit business?

40:17.708 --> 40:18.750
What?

40:19.375 --> 40:21.291
Um… The, uh… drugs.

40:21.791 --> 40:25.416
Oh, that's just temporary.
Saving up to get out of here.

40:25.500 --> 40:27.041
Take me with you.

40:28.416 --> 40:29.875
[whistling]

40:30.791 --> 40:33.208
-[imitates explosion]
-[girls screaming]

40:35.958 --> 40:36.791
[Deena] Run!

40:39.750 --> 40:40.875
Did they get back together?

40:41.875 --> 40:43.750
[screaming]

40:44.333 --> 40:46.041
[all screaming]

40:47.333 --> 40:51.000
[TV host] Tonight's Unsolved Mysteries,
the story of a lonely housewife…

40:53.125 --> 40:56.000
-Where are the keys? Do you have the keys?
-No!

40:56.083 --> 40:57.416
Where… where are the keys?

40:58.625 --> 41:00.458
Come on. The ambulance!

41:01.833 --> 41:03.416
[glass breaking]

41:17.083 --> 41:19.041
[breathing heavily]

41:21.541 --> 41:23.833
[ominous music playing]

41:24.666 --> 41:25.916
[Sam gasps]

41:26.416 --> 41:28.750
[muffled sobs]

41:33.583 --> 41:34.708
[whimpering]

41:34.791 --> 41:37.666
-[Deena whispers] No!
-You can't wear that mask. What are--

41:38.916 --> 41:40.416
[Deena gasps]

41:44.375 --> 41:45.916
[screaming]

41:47.791 --> 41:49.500
[Deena] Look out!

41:49.583 --> 41:52.125
[girls screaming]

41:55.333 --> 41:56.250
Come on!

41:57.000 --> 41:58.416
[Sam grunting]

42:00.458 --> 42:02.875
-[Simon] Come on! Let's go!
-[Josh] Come on!

42:03.708 --> 42:04.708
What the…

42:04.791 --> 42:07.583
[female reporter] Mall employee
Ryan Torres has been identified

42:07.666 --> 42:09.708
as the killer in the mall massacre.

42:10.833 --> 42:12.458
[Josh] Deena! Come on! Deena!

42:12.541 --> 42:16.250
-[Simon] Deena! Hurry up! Let's go!
-[Deena] Go! Go!

42:16.333 --> 42:18.000
-[Simon] We have to go now!
-[Deena] Hurry!

42:18.083 --> 42:19.375
[tires screeching]

42:23.666 --> 42:27.750
[Nick] You have access to the mall.
You are still employed there, correct?

42:27.833 --> 42:30.416
I'mma tell you again.
Somebody planted that.

42:30.500 --> 42:32.083
Those ain't my cans.

42:32.750 --> 42:35.250
You're right, Martin. These…

42:36.625 --> 42:39.041
are actually my cans.

42:39.125 --> 42:41.375
Why would I tag my own place of work?

42:42.125 --> 42:43.291
Come on, man!

42:44.125 --> 42:47.000
Martin, around here,
people show a little respect.

42:47.083 --> 42:48.541
They call me Sheriff Goode.

42:50.500 --> 42:51.583
Sheriff Goode?

42:53.958 --> 42:56.250
More like Sheriff motherfucking Evil!

42:58.000 --> 42:59.583
[Deena] I'm telling you, it was him!

43:00.208 --> 43:02.833
The psycho killer
my colleague shot dead, huh?

43:02.916 --> 43:05.291
Yes! That's what we keep saying!

43:05.375 --> 43:07.833
-What's wrong with you?
-[Nick] Officer Kapinski.

43:09.333 --> 43:11.041
You told me to come to you.

43:13.708 --> 43:17.166
We should not be this close to
the police station in a stolen ambulance.

43:17.250 --> 43:18.916
We're hiding in plain sight.

43:19.000 --> 43:20.458
Yeah, just like Bundy.

43:25.250 --> 43:28.875
Ted Bundy, when he was stalking
his victims, I mean.

43:28.958 --> 43:30.666
OK, didn't he get caught though?

43:30.750 --> 43:35.791
-Well, no. Well, yeah, but--
-Figure this out. I'm gonna take a leak.

43:40.250 --> 43:43.416
-[Josh sighs]
-Why do you know so much about killers?

43:45.083 --> 43:46.416
Know thy enemy, right?

43:50.083 --> 43:52.125
-You hang onto any of that candy?
-[Josh] Yeah.

43:57.541 --> 43:59.083
Then his mask came off.

44:00.208 --> 44:01.125
And you saw him?

44:01.208 --> 44:04.375
Yeah. Yeah, the mall killer, Ryan Torres.

44:08.708 --> 44:09.958
That's Ryan Torres.

44:10.041 --> 44:10.916
[Deena] Yes!

44:11.875 --> 44:13.125
Yes, that's him.

44:13.208 --> 44:17.416
I know, but you guys must have made
a mistake or something. Look…

44:19.541 --> 44:22.083
-I know what I saw.
-OK.

44:22.583 --> 44:24.791
Let me get the right paperwork.

44:26.750 --> 44:28.458
"Dead killer chasing…"

44:28.541 --> 44:31.333
Would you say he was more, uh,
Dawn of the Dead

44:31.416 --> 44:33.500
or Night of the Living Dead?

44:33.583 --> 44:34.416
[Sam] Wait.

44:34.500 --> 44:36.750
-You don't believe us?
-This was a waste of time.

44:36.833 --> 44:41.375
We've had prank calls, we've had reports
of skeleton mask copycats all weekend.

44:41.458 --> 44:44.666
Got a call from the hospital.
Lady sounded worked up.

44:44.750 --> 44:45.833
[Deena gasps]

44:49.666 --> 44:52.500
Uh… wait, I'll… I got it.
Take care of them.

44:52.583 --> 44:54.625
[indistinct police radio chatter]

44:57.458 --> 44:59.250
[Kapinski grunts, coughs]

45:00.458 --> 45:01.625
[Kapinski grunts]

45:09.958 --> 45:11.833
[police siren bleeps]

45:12.583 --> 45:13.791
[police siren bleeps]

45:14.458 --> 45:16.666
[engine revs loudly]

45:16.750 --> 45:17.833
[zip closes]

45:18.833 --> 45:25.666
[girl singing]
♪ You always hurt the one you love ♪

45:25.750 --> 45:30.875
♪ The one you shouldn't hurt at all ♪

45:31.416 --> 45:34.916
This is bullshit. There are bodies
at the hospital. You're gonna see--

45:35.000 --> 45:37.583
Honey, we are so appreciative of this tip.

45:37.666 --> 45:40.916
-The killer is still out there!
-We'll do our damnedest to catch him.

45:41.000 --> 45:43.750
You're a monster!
You're supposed to protect us!

45:43.833 --> 45:47.500
Hey, hey! Young lady, do not test me!

45:47.583 --> 45:49.875
[panting] I'm so sorry, sir.

45:49.958 --> 45:52.166
I have no idea what came over me.

45:54.208 --> 45:55.291
Get out of here!

45:56.333 --> 45:59.458
Go find your boyfriends!
Tell them you need to relax!

46:09.250 --> 46:12.375
[girl singing] ♪ You always take ♪

46:13.708 --> 46:17.000
♪ The sweetest rose ♪

46:18.041 --> 46:23.333
♪ And crush it till the petals fall ♪

46:24.500 --> 46:25.500
[Simon] Hey.

46:25.583 --> 46:27.791
-♪ You always take… ♪
-Are you OK?

46:28.375 --> 46:30.750
Do… do you need help? What the…

46:32.666 --> 46:34.625
-[Simon screams]
-[Sam] Deena, slow down!

46:34.708 --> 46:37.291
-[Sam] What are you doing?
-[Deena] Just walk, fast.

46:38.291 --> 46:39.916
We need to leave.

46:40.000 --> 46:43.625
I think we should stay. We're safe here.
What if that psycho shows up again?

46:43.708 --> 46:45.958
-Then we'll be ready.
-[Sam] What the hell?

46:46.041 --> 46:47.583
Deena, what is that?

46:47.666 --> 46:49.958
Is that the cop's? You stole a cop's gun?

46:50.041 --> 46:51.500
Fuck yeah she did!

46:51.583 --> 46:54.166
-You out of your goddamn mind?
-They didn't believe us.

46:54.250 --> 46:55.416
We're on our own.

46:57.250 --> 46:58.708
Where the hell is Simon?

46:58.791 --> 47:00.875
["You Always Hurt the One You Love"
playing]

47:00.958 --> 47:05.541
♪ You always hurt ♪

47:06.625 --> 47:10.208
♪ The one you love ♪

47:11.375 --> 47:14.166
♪ The one you shouldn't hurt… ♪
-[Simon screams]

47:14.250 --> 47:15.625
[grunting]

47:17.208 --> 47:18.708
[gasping]

47:20.166 --> 47:21.375
[Simon yells]

47:23.041 --> 47:24.833
[gunshots]

47:25.500 --> 47:26.666
[Simon yells]

47:27.708 --> 47:30.208
-Simon, come on!
-[Simon screams]

47:30.291 --> 47:32.416
-[Kate] Come on!
-[Simon] Go! Go! Let's go!

47:33.000 --> 47:34.083
[Simon] Go! Come on!

47:34.833 --> 47:36.916
-Come on!
-[Simon] Sam! Come on! Run!

47:40.250 --> 47:41.833
♪ You always… ♪

47:41.916 --> 47:44.541
[Sam] It doesn't make sense.
It's… it's not possible.

47:44.625 --> 47:47.000
-Bullets didn't stop her.
-Amazing observation.

47:47.083 --> 47:50.291
-Who the hell was that?
-How the hell should I know? She…

47:50.375 --> 47:53.625
She was hot! I don't know!
The bitch seemed normal!

47:53.708 --> 47:55.166
I hate to break it to you,

47:55.250 --> 47:57.791
but normal bitches
don't bleed black fucking blood!

47:57.875 --> 47:59.875
Well, she was hot and normal

47:59.958 --> 48:02.625
until she attacked me
with a fucking razor blade!

48:04.000 --> 48:06.958
Wait. What… A razor?

48:07.041 --> 48:12.375
Yeah, for like old-timey shaving,
or in this case, I guess, slitting her--

48:12.458 --> 48:15.416
Wrists. She slashed her wrists.

48:17.750 --> 48:19.458
Was she singing something?

48:19.541 --> 48:22.458
Was she singing a song, like an oldie…
like an oldie song?

48:22.541 --> 48:26.041
Jesus, Rain Man.
How the fuck do you know that?

48:32.458 --> 48:34.125
This is Ruby Lane.

48:34.208 --> 48:36.916
♪ You always hurt… ♪

48:37.000 --> 48:39.291
-[Josh] The girl who attacked you.
-[Simon] Holy shit!

48:39.375 --> 48:42.000
She sang as she murdered her boyfriend,

48:42.083 --> 48:45.458
her friends, then she killed herself.
Slashed her wrists.

48:45.541 --> 48:48.333
Jesus. Yeah, why didn't I see this
on the news?

48:48.416 --> 48:50.458
Because it happened 30 years ago.

48:51.541 --> 48:53.041
1965.

49:00.375 --> 49:03.458
Ruby is one of Shadyside's killers,
just like Skull Mask.

49:03.958 --> 49:06.791
[Heather] Ryan? Please!

49:07.291 --> 49:09.125
[Josh] I mean Ryan Torres.

49:09.208 --> 49:11.208
Look, 1978.

49:11.291 --> 49:13.208
-[girl screaming]
-[Josh] Sixteen years ago.

49:14.958 --> 49:17.916
-[Josh] "Masked psycho murders kids at--"
-[Kate] Camp Nightwing.

49:18.625 --> 49:20.458
Yeah, my mom's sister was there.

49:20.541 --> 49:22.458
That screwed my family up for a long time.

49:22.541 --> 49:24.041
[Josh] 1950,

49:24.125 --> 49:25.708
Harry Rooker,

49:25.791 --> 49:28.625
local milkman slashes
a bunch of housewives.

49:28.708 --> 49:31.291
1935, Humpty Dumpty Killer.

49:32.416 --> 49:34.875
1922, Billy Barker.

49:35.458 --> 49:39.000
1904, Grifter guts girls, and on and on.

49:39.083 --> 49:42.916
It happens in Shadyside over and over.
Normal people turn into psychos.

49:43.000 --> 49:43.958
[Simon] Jesus.

49:44.041 --> 49:45.833
[indistinct voices whispering]

49:45.916 --> 49:47.416
[Simon] Look at this guy.

49:50.500 --> 49:52.208
That's the pastor, Cyrus Miller.

49:52.291 --> 49:55.000
1666. He was the first one recorded.

49:55.583 --> 49:58.083
He, um… killed kids
and cut out their eyes.

50:03.708 --> 50:05.958
[retching]

50:09.291 --> 50:10.291
[Deena] Sam?

50:15.125 --> 50:17.708
I, uh, brought you…

50:21.916 --> 50:24.166
-I always liked this sweater.
-Yeah, I know.

50:24.750 --> 50:26.708
If you get blood on it, I'll kill you.

50:30.041 --> 50:31.333
What's happening to us?

50:32.333 --> 50:34.583
There are people trying to kill us.

50:35.375 --> 50:38.250
Dead people,
if you believe my weirdo brother.

50:38.833 --> 50:39.666
[scoffs]

50:40.916 --> 50:42.125
That's not what I meant.

50:42.958 --> 50:44.125
Yeah, I know.

50:45.375 --> 50:49.250
Look, I know I always give you shit
for pretending you're someone you're not,

50:49.333 --> 50:50.375
but it's…

50:51.916 --> 50:54.083
It's not really easy for me to…

50:55.666 --> 50:58.875
you know, be like us… either.

51:01.083 --> 51:04.208
-Are you giving me a pass?
-[chuckles] No.

51:08.625 --> 51:11.958
Fine. I'm not gonna say
what I was gonna say.

51:12.041 --> 51:13.083
Say it.

51:16.375 --> 51:17.375
[Sam sighs]

51:17.458 --> 51:19.750
Maybe you're… you're right.

51:19.833 --> 51:21.500
Maybe shit is doomed.

51:22.791 --> 51:26.125
I mean, here we are.
We're together for one night and--

51:26.208 --> 51:28.458
Dead people are trying to kill us.

51:28.541 --> 51:30.333
[Josh] None of this is random.

51:32.166 --> 51:33.375
It's Sarah Fier.

51:33.458 --> 51:35.583
She's turning Shadysiders into killers.

51:36.083 --> 51:37.583
Do you really believe that?

51:38.583 --> 51:41.083
No one actually thinks
that this witch shit is real.

51:41.166 --> 51:44.291
Yeah, it's something babysitters make up
to scare kids.

51:44.375 --> 51:45.750
No, no. Just listen to me.

51:45.833 --> 51:50.083
1666, Sarah Fier was hanged
for witchcraft, fact.

51:50.583 --> 51:53.333
But ever since she was executed,
she's been possessing people,

51:53.416 --> 51:55.958
turning them into killers,
to take revenge on the town.

51:56.041 --> 51:59.000
-[Simon] It's like the nursery rhyme.
-[Josh] Yeah. Yeah.

51:59.083 --> 52:03.083
[Simon] "Before the witch's final breath,
she found a way to cheat her death."

52:04.125 --> 52:06.833
"By cutting off her cursed hand,

52:06.916 --> 52:09.916
she kept her grip upon our land."

52:10.708 --> 52:14.666
"She reaches from beyond the grave

52:15.458 --> 52:18.875
to make good men her wicked slaves."

52:18.958 --> 52:20.500
Yes, exactly.

52:20.583 --> 52:24.166
Don't you see what's happening to us?
This is all proof.

52:24.250 --> 52:26.750
Shadyside isn't just
some hotbed for psychos.

52:26.833 --> 52:29.666
All these massacres are connected
to Sarah Fier.

52:29.750 --> 52:31.250
The witch's curse is real!

52:31.333 --> 52:34.541
Fine. Let's assume that the witch
has been possessing people

52:34.625 --> 52:36.875
for some sort of messed-up vendetta.

52:36.958 --> 52:40.416
This isn't the same as the mall massacre.
Something different is happening to us.

52:40.500 --> 52:41.750
Something way worse.

52:41.833 --> 52:46.125
OK, we have two of her killers after us
and both of them are dead.

52:46.708 --> 52:48.333
Why is she so mad at us?

52:48.416 --> 52:49.416
[Sam] I saw her.

52:51.833 --> 52:53.166
Last night, I don't…

52:54.250 --> 52:57.166
I don't know, you know.
I thought I hit my head…

52:59.250 --> 53:00.291
It was…

53:00.791 --> 53:01.875
It was her.

53:03.958 --> 53:05.416
I saw the witch.

53:05.500 --> 53:06.625
[ominous drumbeat]

53:06.708 --> 53:08.625
[crickets chirping]

53:12.375 --> 53:13.916
I can't believe you're wearing that.

53:14.000 --> 53:15.208
Can't believe you're above it,

53:15.291 --> 53:17.000
when we're in the middle
of the fucking woods

53:17.083 --> 53:18.791
and dead maniacs are after us.

53:18.875 --> 53:20.000
[sighs]

53:23.458 --> 53:24.833
[high-pitched shrill]

53:38.625 --> 53:40.666
OK, so I fell out of the car…

53:41.583 --> 53:42.625
here.

53:44.958 --> 53:46.500
I was crawling,

53:47.041 --> 53:48.916
and my nose was bleeding.

53:49.791 --> 53:50.958
And then…

53:51.041 --> 53:53.000
-[metal clinking]
-I feel something.

53:59.666 --> 54:00.833
[Kate] Chains?

54:04.541 --> 54:06.666
Oh! Not just chains.

54:08.500 --> 54:11.041
-[Kate] Holy shit.
-Oh my gosh.

54:11.125 --> 54:13.291
-No way.
-Oh!

54:19.041 --> 54:21.208
Fier. It's her.

54:22.250 --> 54:23.500
It's her grave.

54:24.000 --> 54:25.750
Oh no, no. No!

54:25.833 --> 54:28.541
This is bad! This is really bad!

54:28.625 --> 54:31.208
No wonder the witch is pissed at us.
I'd be pissed too.

54:31.291 --> 54:32.541
Sam disturbed her grave.

54:34.291 --> 54:36.791
[sighs] Now she's sending
her henchmen after us.

54:37.583 --> 54:38.541
Henchmen?

54:39.750 --> 54:43.000
As in every one of those sickos
on your wall is coming after us?

54:43.083 --> 54:44.375
[twigs snapping]

54:44.958 --> 54:45.916
Did you hear that?

54:46.000 --> 54:47.333
[breathing heavily]

54:49.625 --> 54:50.958
[Simon] Hold up. Hold up.

54:51.041 --> 54:54.583
She's mad
because we disturbed her grave, right?

54:54.666 --> 54:56.375
Yeah. So?

54:56.458 --> 54:59.416
So, let's un-disturb it!

54:59.500 --> 55:02.875
Just put the bones back, rebury them,
and put her to rest!

55:02.958 --> 55:04.583
No, that's so stupid!

55:04.666 --> 55:05.708
That's genius!

55:06.541 --> 55:08.125
Yeah! In… in Poltergeist!

55:08.208 --> 55:09.666
-[twigs snapping]
-[gasping]

55:10.791 --> 55:13.125
Whatever.
Let's do it quickly so we can go.

55:13.208 --> 55:14.625
[dramatic music playing]

55:23.083 --> 55:24.166
[Simon] OK.

55:24.250 --> 55:26.833
Deena, Deena!
Find something to wrap her bones!

55:38.458 --> 55:40.333
[ominous music playing]

55:44.375 --> 55:45.333
[gasps]

55:45.833 --> 55:47.625
[woman] You! It's you!

55:47.708 --> 55:49.291
[screaming] It's you!

55:49.875 --> 55:51.000
[gasps]

55:51.666 --> 55:52.791
Your nose…

55:57.125 --> 55:58.333
[Josh] Guys?

56:01.708 --> 56:03.375
I think there's someone in the woods!

56:03.958 --> 56:05.666
[metal chains clinking]

56:11.708 --> 56:13.041
[woman whispers] It's you!

56:13.625 --> 56:15.000
It's you!

56:16.250 --> 56:17.791
We need to hurry!

56:17.875 --> 56:19.500
There, there.

56:19.583 --> 56:20.916
We're sorry.

56:21.541 --> 56:22.583
Did it work?

56:25.666 --> 56:26.666
Did it work?

56:26.750 --> 56:28.666
[breathing shakily]

56:33.791 --> 56:36.208
[dramatic music playing]

56:36.291 --> 56:37.291
[Josh grunts]

56:40.041 --> 56:42.666
-[Simon] No!
-[woman screams] It's you!

56:42.750 --> 56:45.041
-[screaming]
-[Deena] Go, run!

56:46.833 --> 56:48.666
Run! Run!

56:48.750 --> 56:51.000
Go! Come on, go!

56:51.083 --> 56:52.458
Start the car! Go!

56:52.541 --> 56:55.083
-[engine starts]
-[tires screech]

56:58.625 --> 57:01.500
-That was the Camp Nightwing Killer!
-That was a bust!

57:01.583 --> 57:04.625
Yeah, maybe because
it's not like the movies, OK?

57:04.708 --> 57:07.125
It's not as easy as putting bones to rest!

57:07.208 --> 57:10.916
-It should've worked. It always works!
-[Josh] Maybe it's her missing hand.

57:11.000 --> 57:13.666
Who gives a shit? It doesn't matter.
Hey, how do I not die?

57:13.750 --> 57:15.666
[Simon] We! How do we not die!

57:15.750 --> 57:18.041
And I'm looking at you, witch nerd!

57:18.125 --> 57:20.750
-I… I don't know!
-They're not coming for us!

57:22.750 --> 57:25.541
-They're coming for me.
-What?

57:25.625 --> 57:28.166
-I saw her again…
-[woman whispers] It's you.

57:28.250 --> 57:31.666
The witch. She… I disturbed her grave.

57:32.750 --> 57:34.833
-[woman whispers] It's you.
-She wants me.

57:36.041 --> 57:39.541
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.
Nightwing ran right by me.

57:39.625 --> 57:43.541
I jumped out his way, it was like
he didn't even see me. He went for her.

57:44.208 --> 57:47.250
Guys, no! Ruby attacked Simon.

57:47.333 --> 57:50.916
Skull Mask came after us at home.
And while you guys were babysitting!

57:51.708 --> 57:53.375
[brakes screeching]

57:53.458 --> 57:55.166
No, he didn't.

57:55.250 --> 57:57.250
Skull Mask didn't care about us.

57:57.333 --> 58:00.250
He wanted this. Sam's blood.

58:00.833 --> 58:02.541
-What the fu…
-Oh!

58:02.625 --> 58:06.041
Yeah! From the crash
when Sam puked period!

58:06.125 --> 58:07.666
It's Jaws, dude!

58:07.750 --> 58:09.083
A shark smelling blood!

58:09.166 --> 58:11.833
[panting] Kate's right!
When we found Skeletor,

58:11.916 --> 58:15.458
he was all sniffy and weird with my shirt
like a perv in a pantie shop!

58:15.541 --> 58:17.625
Yeah, but he came to our house too!

58:18.500 --> 58:19.375
[Kate] Deena…

58:23.541 --> 58:26.958
[Simon] Sam bled on her bones,
now the witch wants more of her blood!

58:27.041 --> 58:29.000
OK, so what do they do in Jaws?

58:29.083 --> 58:31.666
They didn't go skinny-dipping
with the goddamn bait.

58:31.750 --> 58:32.750
She's not bait!

58:32.833 --> 58:35.041
Yeah. She is.

58:35.875 --> 58:38.583
Seriously, if we're right
and they're after her…

58:40.041 --> 58:42.125
let's give these assholes what they want.

58:44.250 --> 58:46.125
[sirens wailing]

58:55.791 --> 58:56.875
[sighs]

59:15.250 --> 59:17.250
[menacing music playing]

59:53.458 --> 59:55.541
[Josh] Alright, we have to decontaminate.

59:56.291 --> 59:58.041
You can't have any of Sam's blood on you.

59:58.125 --> 1:00:00.458
Well, not much I can do about that.

1:00:02.916 --> 1:00:05.958
Deena, you have to get clean too!
Not a single drop, OK?

1:00:06.041 --> 1:00:07.875
[Simon] Rub-a-dub-dub time!

1:00:08.791 --> 1:00:09.750
[Kate] Hey, wait.

1:00:11.166 --> 1:00:13.083
I don't want to go in by myself.

1:00:18.500 --> 1:00:19.625
[exhales slowly]

1:00:20.750 --> 1:00:26.125
[whispering] Up, up, down, down.
Left, right, left, right, B, A, start.

1:00:33.750 --> 1:00:35.791
Holy shit, your shoulder.

1:00:36.541 --> 1:00:37.416
It's fine.

1:00:38.416 --> 1:00:39.458
OK, well,

1:00:40.500 --> 1:00:43.125
fine or not, we s… still need to cover it.

1:00:46.958 --> 1:00:49.000
[soft music playing]

1:01:09.791 --> 1:01:12.541
[humming]

1:01:29.875 --> 1:01:32.041
[Kate] Do you really think
this is going to work?

1:01:37.000 --> 1:01:38.000
I do.

1:01:40.458 --> 1:01:41.458
[Kate] Josh…

1:01:42.708 --> 1:01:43.708
Can you help me?

1:01:49.958 --> 1:01:51.958
[dramatic music playing]

1:02:05.125 --> 1:02:06.166
[Sam sighs]

1:02:07.750 --> 1:02:09.166
This is all my fault.

1:02:09.666 --> 1:02:10.791
I'm sorry.

1:02:11.541 --> 1:02:13.208
When I went to Sunnyvale,

1:02:13.875 --> 1:02:15.333
I ran away from you.

1:02:18.375 --> 1:02:19.583
Because you were, like…

1:02:21.541 --> 1:02:22.708
this reminder.

1:02:24.000 --> 1:02:26.250
I was scared of this.

1:02:27.208 --> 1:02:28.208
Of us.

1:02:32.208 --> 1:02:33.208
Of me.

1:02:34.208 --> 1:02:36.291
And, like, tonight's been the first time

1:02:36.375 --> 1:02:38.833
I've felt like myself in…

1:02:39.791 --> 1:02:40.916
months.

1:02:42.125 --> 1:02:43.208
It's been so long.

1:02:44.791 --> 1:02:47.291
I forgot what that… what that felt like.

1:02:56.500 --> 1:02:57.750
You make me feel…

1:02:58.916 --> 1:02:59.916
like me.

1:03:02.791 --> 1:03:06.125
["Sweet Jane" playing]

1:03:15.791 --> 1:03:18.333
♪ Anyone who's ever had a heart ♪

1:03:21.208 --> 1:03:24.875
-♪ Wouldn't turn around and break it… ♪
-[Kate] Make sure my back is clean.

1:03:24.958 --> 1:03:25.791
Yeah.

1:03:26.625 --> 1:03:29.916
-You're gonna have to look at me.
-♪ And anyone who's ever played a part ♪

1:03:32.708 --> 1:03:35.166
♪ Wouldn't turn around and hate it ♪

1:03:38.833 --> 1:03:40.791
♪ Sweet Jane… ♪

1:03:41.666 --> 1:03:44.708
[breathing heavily]

1:03:44.791 --> 1:03:46.500
♪ Sweet Jane ♪

1:03:49.250 --> 1:03:52.125
♪ Oh sweet, sweet Jane… ♪

1:03:52.208 --> 1:03:53.625
I think you're all good.

1:03:55.000 --> 1:03:58.125
♪ You're waiting for Jimmy
Down in the alley ♪

1:04:00.125 --> 1:04:01.125
What if…

1:04:01.208 --> 1:04:04.625
♪ You're waiting there
For him to come back home… ♪

1:04:04.708 --> 1:04:06.208
What if tonight's it for us?

1:04:06.708 --> 1:04:09.958
♪ Waiting down on the corner ♪

1:04:12.208 --> 1:04:15.208
♪ And thinking of ways
To get back home ♪

1:04:19.083 --> 1:04:20.791
♪ Sweet Jane… ♪

1:04:20.875 --> 1:04:22.458
[both panting]

1:04:24.916 --> 1:04:26.666
♪ Sweet Jane ♪

1:04:29.250 --> 1:04:31.750
-♪ Oh sweet, sweet Jane… ♪
-[Deena panting]

1:04:37.000 --> 1:04:38.458
[both panting]

1:04:41.458 --> 1:04:43.875
-♪ Anyone who's ever had-- ♪
-[banging]

1:04:45.375 --> 1:04:46.375
Did you hear that?

1:04:46.458 --> 1:04:48.583
[door creaks open, closes]

1:04:54.291 --> 1:04:55.708
No!

1:04:55.791 --> 1:04:56.750
[Kate] Calm down.

1:04:56.833 --> 1:04:58.375
It was barely first base.

1:05:01.041 --> 1:05:03.083
[Simon] Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

1:05:03.166 --> 1:05:06.583
Did you… all go to pound town?

1:05:12.000 --> 1:05:13.041
Me too!

1:05:14.000 --> 1:05:16.500
["Firestarter" playing]

1:05:17.666 --> 1:05:18.666
Ready?

1:05:20.458 --> 1:05:22.000
[Josh] The trap is simple.

1:05:25.333 --> 1:05:26.458
We set the bait.

1:05:26.541 --> 1:05:29.375
-♪ Hey, hey! ♪
-♪ I'm a firestarter… ♪

1:05:29.458 --> 1:05:30.916
[Josh] The killers go to the blood.

1:05:32.375 --> 1:05:33.375
Then…

1:05:34.291 --> 1:05:37.166
Smile, you son of a bitch!

1:05:42.666 --> 1:05:44.166
Are you sure you want to do this?

1:05:46.750 --> 1:05:48.250
See you on the other side.

1:05:50.791 --> 1:05:52.708
[door creaks]

1:05:55.708 --> 1:05:58.125
[breathing heavily]

1:06:02.458 --> 1:06:05.083
[Sam breathing heavily]

1:06:05.166 --> 1:06:07.166
[ominous music playing]

1:06:18.375 --> 1:06:19.833
[door bangs]

1:06:21.791 --> 1:06:23.708
-[breathes shakily]
-[mop head slops]

1:06:23.833 --> 1:06:25.041
[high-pitched shrill]

1:06:27.708 --> 1:06:29.333
[menacing music playing]

1:06:30.750 --> 1:06:34.000
[breathing heavily]

1:06:40.458 --> 1:06:46.916
[Ruby Lane singing]
♪ You always hurt the one you love ♪

1:06:47.875 --> 1:06:51.625
♪ The one you shouldn't hurt at all ♪

1:06:53.833 --> 1:06:55.833
Dude! She's here! I saw her!

1:06:55.916 --> 1:07:00.000
She was…
She was so sexy, but fucking crazy still!

1:07:00.083 --> 1:07:02.416
She was doing it!
Following the blood trails!

1:07:02.500 --> 1:07:05.166
It's working.
Skull Mask freak, three o'clock.

1:07:10.541 --> 1:07:14.500
[Ruby Lane] ♪ You always hurt the one… ♪

1:07:14.583 --> 1:07:15.500
Ruby.

1:07:15.583 --> 1:07:17.250
♪ …you love ♪

1:07:18.125 --> 1:07:21.000
♪ The one you shouldn't hurt… ♪

1:07:21.083 --> 1:07:22.458
[Kate] This is so dumb.

1:07:22.541 --> 1:07:24.708
If this doesn't work, I will murder you!

1:07:25.916 --> 1:07:27.125
[door opens]

1:07:27.625 --> 1:07:30.416
[ominous music crescendos]

1:07:34.958 --> 1:07:36.500
They're all here.

1:07:40.083 --> 1:07:42.666
[ominous music playing]

1:07:44.083 --> 1:07:46.416
♪ So if I… ♪

1:07:52.875 --> 1:07:54.208
[grunting]

1:08:07.625 --> 1:08:09.083
Go, go, go, go, go!

1:08:20.750 --> 1:08:22.416
[screaming]

1:08:23.083 --> 1:08:25.750
[screaming]

1:08:27.083 --> 1:08:29.375
[desperate screaming]

1:08:31.250 --> 1:08:32.666
[loud explosion]

1:08:32.750 --> 1:08:34.125
[screaming stops]

1:08:35.041 --> 1:08:36.375
[Deena sighs]

1:08:48.166 --> 1:08:49.958
Come back from that, motherfuckers!

1:08:50.041 --> 1:08:51.375
[chuckling]

1:08:52.625 --> 1:08:54.333
[Deena and Simon chuckling]

1:08:56.375 --> 1:08:57.458
Oh!

1:08:59.125 --> 1:09:00.625
[fly buzzing]

1:09:01.458 --> 1:09:02.833
[ominous music playing]

1:09:10.583 --> 1:09:11.583
Guys?

1:09:16.125 --> 1:09:17.208
Holy!

1:09:17.291 --> 1:09:18.708
Run! Run!

1:09:18.791 --> 1:09:19.791
Go! Go!

1:09:22.500 --> 1:09:24.166
[menacing music playing]

1:09:24.250 --> 1:09:25.875
[rumbling]

1:09:28.416 --> 1:09:29.375
Help me!

1:09:33.083 --> 1:09:35.208
-They're coming!
-They're gonna keep coming!

1:09:35.291 --> 1:09:36.250
We're fucked!

1:09:36.333 --> 1:09:38.375
No, no! We are not fucked!

1:09:39.291 --> 1:09:42.125
She's fucked. They're coming for her.

1:09:42.208 --> 1:09:44.833
If we put Sam in the hall,
we end this now.

1:09:44.916 --> 1:09:46.958
-You're a monster.
-I'm being reasonable!

1:09:47.041 --> 1:09:48.583
We can't run anymore.

1:09:48.666 --> 1:09:50.500
A bullet won't stop them, fine.

1:09:50.583 --> 1:09:51.958
They're really strong.

1:09:52.041 --> 1:09:55.750
But we just tried to goddamn explode them,
and that didn't work!

1:09:55.833 --> 1:09:57.333
You're suggesting killing her.

1:09:57.416 --> 1:09:59.791
I mean, that's not exactly
what she's saying.

1:09:59.875 --> 1:10:01.041
Oh, you're on her side?

1:10:01.125 --> 1:10:04.208
You'd let us all die to protect her.
Look at this.

1:10:04.291 --> 1:10:05.541
OK, all of this.

1:10:05.625 --> 1:10:07.875
Dead, dead, dead!

1:10:09.083 --> 1:10:10.125
This is the way.

1:10:10.625 --> 1:10:12.375
It's the only way.

1:10:17.416 --> 1:10:18.458
Sam's gotta go.

1:10:21.875 --> 1:10:23.208
Are you kidding me?

1:10:26.750 --> 1:10:28.666
[inhales deeply] Kate's right.

1:10:29.791 --> 1:10:31.625
I don't want you guys to die for me.

1:10:35.083 --> 1:10:36.083
I'm going.

1:10:38.958 --> 1:10:39.875
I'm ending this.

1:10:39.958 --> 1:10:41.208
No, you're not.

1:10:41.708 --> 1:10:42.750
Are you crazy?

1:10:47.083 --> 1:10:48.208
No.

1:10:50.416 --> 1:10:51.458
No, Sam!

1:10:51.541 --> 1:10:52.708
Sam!

1:10:52.791 --> 1:10:54.000
Sam!

1:10:54.083 --> 1:10:55.791
Let me go! Let me… Sam!

1:11:01.250 --> 1:11:03.375
[breathing heavily]

1:11:04.250 --> 1:11:06.083
[breathing heavily]

1:11:10.166 --> 1:11:11.625
[grunting]

1:11:11.708 --> 1:11:14.333
[breathing heavily]

1:11:15.166 --> 1:11:17.000
[Deena] Let me go. Let me go!

1:11:17.083 --> 1:11:19.708
Let me… Help me! Help!

1:11:19.791 --> 1:11:21.625
[ominous music playing]

1:11:21.708 --> 1:11:23.708
[breathing heavily]

1:11:23.791 --> 1:11:25.000
[snorts]

1:11:26.833 --> 1:11:28.500
[breathing heavily]

1:11:28.583 --> 1:11:30.083
[Deena] We're letting her die!

1:11:30.708 --> 1:11:32.000
We're killing her!

1:11:32.791 --> 1:11:34.208
[sobbing] Please!

1:11:34.291 --> 1:11:35.958
[quietly] This is not your fault.

1:11:37.833 --> 1:11:40.166
[Deena crying] Please!

1:11:40.250 --> 1:11:41.208
Please!

1:11:41.291 --> 1:11:44.416
[dramatic music playing]

1:11:45.791 --> 1:11:48.541
[snorting]

1:11:48.625 --> 1:11:51.000
[breathing heavily]

1:11:55.416 --> 1:11:56.875
-[Sam screams]
-[he roars]

1:11:56.958 --> 1:12:01.208
-[Sam] What… what… what is going on?
-[Kate] You're not doing this alone.

1:12:01.291 --> 1:12:03.166
-[Josh] There's another way.
-[pounding on door]

1:12:03.250 --> 1:12:05.166
-C. Berman.
-[pounding continues]

1:12:05.708 --> 1:12:06.791
She's the key.

1:12:10.041 --> 1:12:12.666
[Sam] Camp Nightwing. Summer of '78.

1:12:12.750 --> 1:12:15.083
Group of campers, brutal massacre.

1:12:15.166 --> 1:12:17.208
There was one Shadyside survivor,
C. Berman.

1:12:17.291 --> 1:12:21.500
"The still traumatized girl claims that
amidst the carnage she saw the witch."

1:12:21.583 --> 1:12:25.291
Yeah, just like you.
So, if she survived, I'm pretty sure--

1:12:25.375 --> 1:12:27.166
There may be a way for me to live too.

1:12:27.250 --> 1:12:30.416
[Kate] I got it! C. Berman!
9006 Brennan Way.

1:12:30.500 --> 1:12:31.791
This has gotta be her!

1:12:33.250 --> 1:12:35.291
Uh, 155-4747!

1:12:37.291 --> 1:12:39.291
[ringing tone]

1:12:39.375 --> 1:12:41.916
-No one's answering!
-[voicemail] The Berman residence.

1:12:42.000 --> 1:12:44.500
-I'm not home right now.
-I need some help here!

1:12:44.583 --> 1:12:47.375
-Please leave a message after the beep.
-No one's there!

1:12:47.458 --> 1:12:50.500
Hello, my name is Deena Johnson.
I think you saw the witch.

1:12:51.000 --> 1:12:51.958
[Simon grunts]

1:12:53.833 --> 1:12:55.375
This shit is not gonna hold!

1:12:55.458 --> 1:12:56.958
We need to know how you survived!

1:12:57.041 --> 1:12:59.916
Hey! We're being attacked, alright?
There are killers here!

1:13:00.000 --> 1:13:03.541
If you're there, please pick up!
Please answer!

1:13:03.625 --> 1:13:07.083
-To record a new message, press one.
-Fuck! No!

1:13:07.666 --> 1:13:09.750
-[Simon screams]
-[Kate] Help!

1:13:11.708 --> 1:13:13.666
-[Kate] Help us!
-[Simon] Help!

1:13:13.750 --> 1:13:15.208
[Josh grunts]

1:13:17.250 --> 1:13:19.500
-[ringing tone]
-[Sam] She died.

1:13:20.208 --> 1:13:22.083
[pounding on door]

1:13:22.166 --> 1:13:23.083
She died.

1:13:23.958 --> 1:13:26.083
What? No, she's alive.
That's the whole point.

1:13:26.166 --> 1:13:28.458
Yeah, she… she survived, but…

1:13:29.125 --> 1:13:30.458
but first she died.

1:13:30.541 --> 1:13:31.958
[pounding on door]

1:13:33.583 --> 1:13:35.208
[Deena] "C. Berman was found
in the woods."

1:13:35.291 --> 1:13:38.208
"Her heart had stopped
but local boy performed CPR."

1:13:39.291 --> 1:13:40.583
What if this is it?

1:13:41.416 --> 1:13:44.500
What if that's how she survived?
Her heart stopped.

1:13:44.583 --> 1:13:46.583
She survived by dying.

1:13:46.666 --> 1:13:49.666
What is it? The fucking rhyme.
The fucking rhyme!

1:13:49.750 --> 1:13:51.916
"She'll take your blood,
she'll take your head!"

1:13:52.000 --> 1:13:54.416
-"She'll follow you--"
-"Until you're dead."

1:13:54.500 --> 1:13:57.166
-[pounding continues]
-It's just like Kate said. OK?

1:13:57.250 --> 1:13:58.791
The witch wants you dead.

1:13:58.875 --> 1:14:01.583
So… we kill you.

1:14:02.625 --> 1:14:06.541
And then, just like this C. Berman bitch,
we bring you back to life.

1:14:06.625 --> 1:14:07.708
What are you saying?

1:14:07.791 --> 1:14:09.958
[dramatic music playing]

1:14:12.083 --> 1:14:15.416
Fuck it. I'm dying tonight
one way or another.

1:14:16.500 --> 1:14:17.916
Let's try to bring me back.

1:14:25.708 --> 1:14:27.041
[breathing heavily]

1:14:28.291 --> 1:14:30.000
-[Simon] Let's do it!
-[Deena screams]

1:14:30.083 --> 1:14:32.083
[ominous music playing]

1:14:33.791 --> 1:14:35.208
Let's Timothy this bitch!

1:14:35.291 --> 1:14:36.750
[tires screeching]

1:14:59.333 --> 1:15:01.625
[soft menacing music]

1:15:02.291 --> 1:15:03.291
[clicks pen]

1:15:09.166 --> 1:15:11.541
[soft menacing music intensifies]

1:15:13.458 --> 1:15:16.083
[menacing music crescendos]

1:15:23.833 --> 1:15:25.416
[ominous music playing]

1:15:37.541 --> 1:15:41.750
A few months ago, my brother Timothy
had an unfortunate experience

1:15:41.833 --> 1:15:45.375
in which he ingested too much
of a certain substance.

1:15:45.458 --> 1:15:48.250
He was dead for two minutes.

1:15:48.333 --> 1:15:49.250
But…

1:15:51.041 --> 1:15:52.125
we got him back!

1:15:53.208 --> 1:15:54.250
[Deena] Kate.

1:15:55.166 --> 1:15:56.875
It's time for your close-up.

1:16:00.833 --> 1:16:04.833
You need to take these in order.
Pile one takes the edge off.

1:16:04.916 --> 1:16:07.958
You're gonna feel like
you're being fucked by a unicorn.

1:16:08.916 --> 1:16:12.666
Pile two is gonna bring
your core temp way down.

1:16:12.750 --> 1:16:13.958
You may feel slightly sick.

1:16:16.083 --> 1:16:19.458
You need to take a five-minute interval
between pile two and pile three.

1:16:19.541 --> 1:16:22.583
That's really important, OK?
Pile three brings you down and out,

1:16:22.666 --> 1:16:25.166
so take that "take five"
or it's all gonna go to shit!

1:16:26.583 --> 1:16:28.541
-How many do we have?
-Tons. Like a thousand.

1:16:28.625 --> 1:16:29.833
Wait. EpiPens?

1:16:29.916 --> 1:16:32.375
Epinephrine, also known as adrenaline.

1:16:32.458 --> 1:16:35.250
This is what brings her back.
This is Jesus!

1:16:36.833 --> 1:16:37.916
[sighs]

1:16:38.750 --> 1:16:40.375
[Deena] Sam's blood marks the spot.

1:16:51.000 --> 1:16:53.541
Remember half an hour ago,
when you wanted to murder me?

1:16:54.125 --> 1:16:56.458
You don't have to do this. You can leave.

1:16:57.125 --> 1:16:59.625
Remember when you decided
to sacrifice yourself for us?

1:17:00.291 --> 1:17:01.666
We're ending this together.

1:17:04.333 --> 1:17:05.791
Die well, my friend.

1:17:08.166 --> 1:17:09.375
We got back door patrol.

1:17:11.625 --> 1:17:12.541
[Kate] Hey!

1:17:21.000 --> 1:17:22.625
I'll run interference up here.

1:17:29.166 --> 1:17:30.541
[ominous drumbeat]

1:17:31.416 --> 1:17:34.250
OK, I got stock room.
You take the emergency exit.

1:17:34.333 --> 1:17:37.500
Whoa! No, no, no!
Splitting up is not a good idea at all.

1:17:37.583 --> 1:17:41.041
But, dude, listen to me.
I know that this is all fucked,

1:17:41.125 --> 1:17:42.958
but… we gotta do this.

1:17:44.250 --> 1:17:45.250
Kate,

1:17:46.500 --> 1:17:47.791
she's a crusher.

1:17:47.875 --> 1:17:50.333
She doesn't have time for most people.

1:17:51.500 --> 1:17:52.500
I know.

1:17:53.875 --> 1:17:56.333
She's being nice
because we're probably gonna die.

1:17:56.416 --> 1:17:57.541
No! OK, well…

1:17:58.958 --> 1:18:00.750
maybe we're gonna die,

1:18:00.833 --> 1:18:03.291
but Kate is not nice.

1:18:04.625 --> 1:18:07.000
She sees something in you.

1:18:09.083 --> 1:18:12.958
-So?
-So, see that in yourself, dude.

1:18:13.041 --> 1:18:16.291
We would not be this far
if it weren't for you.

1:18:17.500 --> 1:18:21.250
Now we have to keep those psychos
away from Sam.

1:18:21.333 --> 1:18:22.333
So go…

1:18:22.833 --> 1:18:24.250
[slaps shoulder] …man up,

1:18:24.833 --> 1:18:26.166
and check that exit.

1:18:32.791 --> 1:18:33.875
[Sam] Deena.

1:18:34.708 --> 1:18:35.625
Deena.

1:18:37.458 --> 1:18:39.166
What if we fuck up and just kill me?

1:18:40.375 --> 1:18:42.750
What if you can't bring me back?
[sniffles]

1:18:43.666 --> 1:18:44.666
Listen to me.

1:18:45.916 --> 1:18:47.083
When you left,

1:18:47.166 --> 1:18:48.333
I saw it all.

1:18:48.416 --> 1:18:49.708
My whole future,

1:18:49.791 --> 1:18:52.583
my whole life in Shadyside.

1:18:52.666 --> 1:18:55.000
A night shift, a day shift,

1:18:55.083 --> 1:18:57.250
and a million empty beer cans,

1:18:57.916 --> 1:18:59.125
just like my dad.

1:19:00.125 --> 1:19:01.375
No way out.

1:19:01.958 --> 1:19:04.416
But tonight, even though we are in hell,

1:19:05.416 --> 1:19:08.000
I feel like I have
another chance with you.

1:19:08.916 --> 1:19:10.583
And I'm not gonna lose you again.

1:19:11.583 --> 1:19:13.500
Because you, and we,

1:19:13.583 --> 1:19:15.083
are the way out.

1:19:16.958 --> 1:19:20.541
When this is all over,
I am gonna take you on a date.

1:19:20.625 --> 1:19:22.500
[both chuckling]

1:19:23.166 --> 1:19:26.666
We're going to eat cheeseburgers
and listen to the Pixies,

1:19:27.333 --> 1:19:32.208
and make out and have
the best night of our goddamn lives.

1:19:34.291 --> 1:19:36.125
But right now, you've got to die.

1:19:37.458 --> 1:19:39.458
Now, look at me. Look at me.

1:19:40.625 --> 1:19:42.708
I am going to bring you back.

1:19:44.208 --> 1:19:45.250
[sighs]

1:19:46.166 --> 1:19:50.375
[Sam breathes heavily]

1:20:19.833 --> 1:20:21.625
[metal clanging]

1:20:24.125 --> 1:20:25.833
[eerie music playing]

1:20:52.666 --> 1:20:57.500
[breathing rapidly]

1:20:59.291 --> 1:21:01.083
[loud bang]

1:21:15.333 --> 1:21:20.375
[Sam mumbling, groaning]

1:21:27.583 --> 1:21:28.833
[Sam groaning]

1:21:30.333 --> 1:21:31.291
[Sam croaks]

1:21:31.875 --> 1:21:34.583
-Swallow it. Swallow it.
-[Sam groaning]

1:21:34.666 --> 1:21:36.500
Swallow it. Swallow it.

1:21:37.708 --> 1:21:38.875
[Sam groans]

1:21:41.500 --> 1:21:44.583
[Ruby Lane singing in distance]
♪ You always hurt ♪

1:21:46.166 --> 1:21:49.250
♪ The one you love ♪

1:21:50.416 --> 1:21:55.625
♪ The one you shouldn't hurt at all ♪

1:21:56.958 --> 1:21:59.708
♪ You always take ♪

1:22:05.375 --> 1:22:09.166
[heavy footsteps]

1:22:12.125 --> 1:22:13.916
[Deena] Oh, come on!

1:22:14.000 --> 1:22:15.375
[panting] Come on!

1:22:15.458 --> 1:22:17.083
[Deena panting]

1:22:17.166 --> 1:22:18.416
[groaning]

1:22:20.708 --> 1:22:22.208
[retching]

1:22:25.375 --> 1:22:26.750
I'm so sorry.

1:22:26.833 --> 1:22:30.291
-It's OK. It's OK.
-[crying] I'm so sorry.

1:22:31.541 --> 1:22:33.291
[whimpering]

1:22:33.375 --> 1:22:35.083
-[Sam] Look.
-Huh?

1:22:35.958 --> 1:22:38.666
Look. Behind… behind you!

1:22:39.916 --> 1:22:41.416
[screams]

1:22:41.500 --> 1:22:42.833
Go! Go! Go!

1:22:43.666 --> 1:22:44.583
Go!

1:22:44.666 --> 1:22:45.958
[Deena] Oh!

1:22:51.166 --> 1:22:54.208
[Sam] I need to die. I need to die.

1:22:54.291 --> 1:22:56.541
[Deena] I'm gonna figure this out!

1:22:57.041 --> 1:23:00.250
[ominous music crescendos]

1:23:01.041 --> 1:23:01.958
Go, go!

1:23:04.083 --> 1:23:06.833
[panting]

1:23:10.875 --> 1:23:11.875
[gasps]

1:23:12.916 --> 1:23:16.041
[breathing heavily]

1:23:23.083 --> 1:23:26.375
[breathing heavily]

1:23:29.000 --> 1:23:31.833
[panicked breathing]

1:23:32.916 --> 1:23:33.916
[screams]

1:23:34.000 --> 1:23:35.000
[he grunts]

1:23:39.666 --> 1:23:40.791
[bread slicer whirring]

1:23:41.958 --> 1:23:43.583
[Kate screaming]

1:23:43.666 --> 1:23:45.625
[Kate screaming]

1:23:45.708 --> 1:23:48.000
[Kate] No! No!

1:23:48.583 --> 1:23:49.583
No!

1:23:51.666 --> 1:23:52.791
[Kate] No!

1:23:53.291 --> 1:23:54.791
No!

1:23:54.875 --> 1:23:56.041
Finish it.

1:23:56.125 --> 1:23:58.875
[Kate screaming] No! No!

1:24:16.541 --> 1:24:17.958
[Kate screams]

1:24:23.291 --> 1:24:25.666
[ominous music playing]

1:24:31.916 --> 1:24:33.541
[metal clanging]

1:24:35.000 --> 1:24:38.083
[footsteps approaching]

1:24:39.291 --> 1:24:41.250
-[monster roars]
-[Josh screams]

1:24:43.291 --> 1:24:44.541
[panting]

1:24:45.625 --> 1:24:49.375
[Deena] Do it! Do it! Do it! Come on!

1:24:49.458 --> 1:24:50.875
[Kate screams]

1:24:52.083 --> 1:24:53.375
[screaming]

1:24:54.041 --> 1:24:55.750
[choking]

1:24:56.416 --> 1:24:57.958
[Kate yells]

1:25:00.500 --> 1:25:01.625
[Kate yells]

1:25:03.625 --> 1:25:04.833
[Kate choking]

1:25:05.458 --> 1:25:07.375
[Kate] No! No! No!

1:25:08.625 --> 1:25:11.458
[Kate screaming]

1:25:11.541 --> 1:25:14.125
-[bread slicer whirring]
-[Kate screaming]

1:25:16.583 --> 1:25:19.250
No! No!

1:25:20.708 --> 1:25:22.875
No! No!

1:25:30.083 --> 1:25:32.375
-Go! She's right behind me!
-[Josh gasps]

1:25:35.708 --> 1:25:36.791
[Simon panting]

1:25:37.916 --> 1:25:39.208
[panting]

1:25:43.041 --> 1:25:44.708
[gasping]

1:25:48.166 --> 1:25:49.250
[camp killer roars]

1:25:50.291 --> 1:25:51.625
[Josh screams]

1:25:55.416 --> 1:25:56.541
Come on, Sam!

1:25:57.666 --> 1:26:00.583
[suspenseful music playing]

1:26:15.875 --> 1:26:18.000
-[Deena] Come on, Sam!
-[Sam gurgles]

1:26:19.000 --> 1:26:20.791
[panting, grunts]

1:26:20.875 --> 1:26:22.958
[suspenseful music intensifies]

1:26:29.333 --> 1:26:31.083
♪ You always… ♪

1:26:33.666 --> 1:26:36.375
No! No!

1:26:38.208 --> 1:26:41.166
[ominous music intensifies]

1:26:45.541 --> 1:26:47.875
[high-pitched ringing]

1:26:47.958 --> 1:26:50.625
-[electricity buzzing]
-[Deena sighs]

1:26:51.333 --> 1:26:52.166
[Deena] Sam?

1:26:52.250 --> 1:26:53.708
[electricity buzzing]

1:26:56.083 --> 1:26:57.791
-[electrical thud]
-[Deena gasps]

1:26:57.875 --> 1:26:59.958
[Deena gasping]

1:27:00.041 --> 1:27:02.208
[Josh breathing shakily]

1:27:03.875 --> 1:27:07.166
Josh, Josh! Come help me! Get the pens!

1:27:07.250 --> 1:27:08.666
Get the pens!

1:27:08.750 --> 1:27:10.666
Help me! Go get the EpiPens!

1:27:11.250 --> 1:27:12.416
Come!

1:27:12.500 --> 1:27:13.750
[Josh panting]

1:27:15.583 --> 1:27:16.916
Come, hurry!

1:27:17.000 --> 1:27:19.666
[Josh panting]

1:27:21.666 --> 1:27:23.833
[Deena gasping] Sam!

1:27:26.375 --> 1:27:27.791
Here, here, here!

1:27:34.791 --> 1:27:36.000
Are you doing it right?

1:27:36.083 --> 1:27:38.166
I don't know. I don't know.

1:27:39.375 --> 1:27:40.625
[Deena grunts]

1:27:41.625 --> 1:27:43.583
I don't think it's working.

1:27:43.666 --> 1:27:46.000
It has to work! It has to.

1:27:46.708 --> 1:27:49.000
It has to. Sam?

1:27:49.083 --> 1:27:51.416
[Deena gasping] Sam?

1:27:51.500 --> 1:27:53.500
[ethereal music playing]

1:27:56.791 --> 1:27:58.041
[crying] Everyone's dead.

1:28:00.500 --> 1:28:01.666
Simon…

1:28:02.916 --> 1:28:04.000
Kate…

1:28:04.625 --> 1:28:06.541
No. No, Sam!

1:28:07.083 --> 1:28:09.791
I will not let you do this.

1:28:12.208 --> 1:28:13.375
Come on!

1:28:13.458 --> 1:28:14.916
[Deena grunting]

1:28:15.000 --> 1:28:16.125
Come on.

1:28:18.375 --> 1:28:19.416
Come on, Sam.

1:28:19.500 --> 1:28:21.666
One, two, three.

1:28:21.750 --> 1:28:24.541
[grunting] Come on, Sam.
Come on. Come on, Sam!

1:28:24.625 --> 1:28:26.833
One, two, three, four.

1:28:26.916 --> 1:28:30.458
One, two, three, four.

1:28:30.541 --> 1:28:32.541
[ethereal music intensifies]

1:28:37.083 --> 1:28:38.916
[retching, coughing]

1:28:42.708 --> 1:28:43.708
[coughing]

1:28:51.583 --> 1:28:52.958
[Deena] It's over.

1:28:55.458 --> 1:28:56.875
[gasping] It's over.

1:28:57.916 --> 1:28:59.041
[sighs]

1:28:59.583 --> 1:29:00.500
[Deena] It's OK.

1:29:01.291 --> 1:29:03.583
It's over. It's over.

1:29:03.666 --> 1:29:07.875
[Deena gasping]

1:29:11.875 --> 1:29:14.791
[Nick] Interview with Deena Johnson.

1:29:14.875 --> 1:29:18.083
Sunday, October 2nd, 1994.

1:29:18.166 --> 1:29:19.583
Wanna tell me what happened?

1:29:20.375 --> 1:29:23.083
We were picking up Sam's prescription.

1:29:23.166 --> 1:29:26.541
And the lights went out.
It was pitch black.

1:29:26.625 --> 1:29:29.125
I couldn't really see anything.

1:29:29.208 --> 1:29:30.500
We ducked behind a counter.

1:29:30.583 --> 1:29:32.041
We hid until it was over.

1:29:33.083 --> 1:29:34.250
How'd you get that?

1:29:36.583 --> 1:29:38.083
I fell on some glass.

1:29:38.166 --> 1:29:40.708
[clears throat] Fell on some glass.

1:29:41.208 --> 1:29:43.541
[Nick] You had 15 stitches
in your shoulder.

1:29:44.041 --> 1:29:45.125
I fell on some glass.

1:29:46.875 --> 1:29:51.333
Sam, you look like a ghost.
Like you just came back from the dead.

1:29:53.333 --> 1:29:54.333
Shock, I guess.

1:29:57.875 --> 1:29:59.958
I'll tell you what the facts tell me.

1:30:00.041 --> 1:30:02.416
-[inhales deeply] The junkies--
-Kate and Simon?

1:30:02.500 --> 1:30:03.833
They weren't junkies.

1:30:05.333 --> 1:30:06.500
They were my friends.

1:30:06.583 --> 1:30:11.000
They're to blame for everything.
That feels too easy to me.

1:30:11.083 --> 1:30:13.875
But that's the story
this department will go with

1:30:13.958 --> 1:30:16.583
unless you can help me
to see it differently.

1:30:18.875 --> 1:30:21.125
Another Shadyside tragedy.

1:30:21.208 --> 1:30:24.500
An underprivileged overachiever
with bright prospects.

1:30:26.250 --> 1:30:31.666
A guy who's been supporting
his family alone since he was 15.

1:30:33.250 --> 1:30:37.208
Both succumbing
to the quick cash of drugs.

1:30:38.208 --> 1:30:40.125
Fits the narrative, right?

1:30:41.833 --> 1:30:44.208
[inhale deeply] Nice and neat.

1:30:49.166 --> 1:30:51.250
[Nick] You came here for my help.

1:30:51.333 --> 1:30:53.500
I should have listened to you. I'm sorry.

1:30:54.833 --> 1:30:56.208
I'm listening now.

1:30:56.750 --> 1:30:58.791
But there's nothing else to say.

1:31:01.791 --> 1:31:03.833
Do you want your friends
going down for this?

1:31:03.916 --> 1:31:04.958
No.

1:31:06.208 --> 1:31:07.416
But they're dead.

1:31:09.708 --> 1:31:12.500
[indistinct police radio chatter]

1:31:12.583 --> 1:31:13.541
[whispers] Hey.

1:31:13.625 --> 1:31:15.791
[whistles] Urkel. Help me out?

1:31:17.291 --> 1:31:18.291
Oh, OK.

1:31:18.375 --> 1:31:20.291
So I'm a bad guy because I'm in here.

1:31:20.791 --> 1:31:23.458
Then that makes you a bad guy, too,
little man.

1:31:36.500 --> 1:31:37.583
[coughs]

1:31:43.083 --> 1:31:44.083
Let's go.

1:31:50.750 --> 1:31:51.875
[whispers] I owe you.

1:31:54.916 --> 1:31:57.500
-[coughs]
-Anything comes to you, call me.

1:32:01.000 --> 1:32:02.000
[prisoner sighs]

1:32:04.708 --> 1:32:05.875
[Nick scoffs]

1:32:06.958 --> 1:32:08.541
Prodigal son returns.

1:32:08.625 --> 1:32:10.208
Man, you ain't my family.

1:32:15.208 --> 1:32:16.208
[woman] Sam!

1:32:17.500 --> 1:32:18.541
Samantha!

1:32:22.041 --> 1:32:23.333
[Deena] So I guess I'll…

1:32:24.625 --> 1:32:26.000
see you tomorrow?

1:32:30.875 --> 1:32:31.875
[sighs]

1:32:33.500 --> 1:32:34.333
No.

1:32:38.416 --> 1:32:39.416
See you tonight.

1:32:51.583 --> 1:32:52.708
[mother] Come on!

1:33:02.083 --> 1:33:03.791
[female reporter 1]
More death in Shadyside.

1:33:03.875 --> 1:33:07.416
A drug-fueled night of violence
leaves a trail of bodies.

1:33:07.500 --> 1:33:08.958
Melissa, give us a recap.

1:33:09.041 --> 1:33:11.583
[female reporter 2] There are
three dead at East Union Medical…

1:33:11.666 --> 1:33:14.666
[Deena] I, uh… I wanted…

1:33:14.750 --> 1:33:17.166
I wanted to give you this the other day.

1:33:17.750 --> 1:33:19.500
-But, uh--
-[Sam] What is this?

1:33:19.583 --> 1:33:20.750
Um…

1:33:21.791 --> 1:33:23.333
-A mixtape?
-Yeah.

1:33:23.416 --> 1:33:25.916
But you don't have to open it right now.

1:33:32.208 --> 1:33:33.166
I knew it.

1:33:39.625 --> 1:33:44.750
["Hey" playing over stereo]
♪ Hey! Been trying to meet you ♪

1:33:47.333 --> 1:33:49.708
♪ Mmm-mmm-mmm ♪

1:33:51.333 --> 1:33:55.958
♪ Hey! Must be a devil between us ♪

1:33:56.041 --> 1:33:58.166
♪ Or whores in my head ♪

1:33:58.833 --> 1:34:00.750
♪ Whores at the door ♪

1:34:01.291 --> 1:34:03.458
♪ Whore in my bed ♪

1:34:03.541 --> 1:34:05.625
-♪ But hey! ♪
-[doorbell rings]

1:34:06.333 --> 1:34:12.458
♪ Where have you been? ♪

1:34:12.541 --> 1:34:14.083
[doorbell rings]

1:34:14.666 --> 1:34:16.208
♪ If you go… ♪

1:34:16.791 --> 1:34:18.791
[Deena] Josh, someone's at the door!

1:34:19.291 --> 1:34:20.416
Josh!

1:34:21.583 --> 1:34:23.000
-[Josh] What?
-[Deena gasps]

1:34:27.666 --> 1:34:30.125
You ordered dinner?

1:34:30.708 --> 1:34:33.250
Yeah, it's not a big deal.
Just some pizza.

1:34:33.333 --> 1:34:34.333
[chuckles]

1:34:36.208 --> 1:34:38.041
[Josh] Ah! Stop! Don't be weird!

1:34:43.958 --> 1:34:45.541
[telephone ringing]

1:34:46.583 --> 1:34:47.500
[telephone ringing]

1:34:48.166 --> 1:34:49.166
Hello?

1:34:53.375 --> 1:34:54.375
Hello?

1:34:55.875 --> 1:34:57.958
Alright. Listen, asshole.
Don't call here--

1:34:58.041 --> 1:34:59.291
[woman] You're still alive!

1:34:59.375 --> 1:35:01.291
[ominous music playing]

1:35:01.375 --> 1:35:02.375
Who is this?

1:35:02.875 --> 1:35:05.583
-[whispering voice echoes] Sam…
-[woman] You called me.

1:35:05.666 --> 1:35:08.708
Wanted to know how I survived
the Camp Nightwing Massacre.

1:35:09.666 --> 1:35:11.041
C. Berman.

1:35:11.125 --> 1:35:14.541
[C. Berman] Did you touch the bones?
Did you see her face?

1:35:14.625 --> 1:35:16.666
-No. It's over.
-[C. Berman] Over?

1:35:16.750 --> 1:35:20.583
Yeah, but, uh…
thanks for your prompt reply.

1:35:20.666 --> 1:35:22.666
-[C. Berman] It's not over.
-[whispering voice] Sam…

1:35:22.750 --> 1:35:24.416
[C. Berman] It's never over.

1:35:25.166 --> 1:35:26.208
We ended it.

1:35:27.041 --> 1:35:28.583
We stopped the killers.

1:35:28.666 --> 1:35:30.416
[C. Berman] But you haven't stopped her.

1:35:30.958 --> 1:35:32.083
You can't.

1:35:32.958 --> 1:35:34.666
She makes the rules.

1:35:34.750 --> 1:35:36.875
[ominous music playing]

1:35:36.958 --> 1:35:37.958
Who?

1:35:38.958 --> 1:35:40.041
[C. Berman] The witch.

1:35:40.541 --> 1:35:42.125
[ominous music plays]

1:35:43.458 --> 1:35:45.291
[C. Berman] She'll do whatever it takes.

1:35:45.375 --> 1:35:48.416
[ritualistic chanting]

1:35:48.500 --> 1:35:49.916
[C. Berman] You're not safe.

1:35:54.291 --> 1:35:55.500
She'll find a way.

1:35:56.083 --> 1:35:58.500
[ritualistic singing intensifies]

1:36:03.666 --> 1:36:05.083
[C. Berman] She'll come for you.

1:36:08.208 --> 1:36:09.875
[gasps, relieved sigh]

1:36:09.958 --> 1:36:11.083
Sam.

1:36:11.166 --> 1:36:12.500
[fly buzzing]

1:36:12.583 --> 1:36:13.583
[gasps]

1:36:20.791 --> 1:36:22.416
[fly buzzing]

1:36:25.708 --> 1:36:27.791
[chat beeping]

1:36:27.875 --> 1:36:31.458
["The Day I Tried To Live"
playing over stereo]

1:36:32.291 --> 1:36:37.166
♪ And gave it to the rich, yeah ♪

1:36:38.708 --> 1:36:41.833
♪ The day I tried to win ♪

1:36:41.916 --> 1:36:45.541
♪ I dangled from the power lines ♪

